race.description: Boxing Day Tickets On Sale Now Maiden Plate
race.comment: CANSORT (4) Tassort colt from Canossa on debut for the Chris Waller yard. Given the three trials and finds a very weak Maiden to get off the mark. Lugging bit goes on from the good gate. OUTDOOR CAT (7) has her hoof on the till fourth-up. Closed strongly with the 58kg when fourth over 1200m at the Sunshine Coast. Well drawn with the claim and shapes as the main danger. ADEQUATE EZE (3) well supported on debut when slow into stride for a battling second over 1210m at Lismore. Will go back from the gate and relish the extra distance. PULIGNY (11) first-up after nine months failed to make an impression in the soft going when sixth over 120m at the Gold Coast. Finds an easier contest and goes into the exotics.
